We can read more tables from the CMI-PB database 

```{r}
specimen <- read_json("http://cmi-pb.org/api/v5_1/specimen",
                      simplifyVector = T)
ab_titer <- read_json("http://cmi-pb.org/api/v5_1/plasma_ab_titer",
                      simplifyVector = T)
```

```{r}
head(specimen)
```
```{r}
head(ab_titer)
```
To make sense of all this data we need to "join" all these tables together. Only then will we know that a given AB mesurment (from the `ab_titer` table) was collectd on a certain data (from the `spcimen` table) from a certain wP or aP subject (from the `subject` table)

we can use **dplyer** and the `*join()` family of functuons to do this. 
```{r}
library(dplyr)
meta <- inner_join(subject, specimen)
head(meta)
```
Let's do one more `inner_join()` to join the `ab_titter` with all out `meta` data
```{r}
abdata <- inner_join(ab_titer,meta)
head(abdata)
```



