# Examine IgG Ab titer levels

> Q13. Complete the following code to make a summary boxplot of Ab titer levels (MFI) for all antigens:

Make a plot of `MFI_normalised` values for all antigen

```{r}
ggplot(igg) +
  aes(MFI_normalised, antigen) + 
  geom_boxplot()
```
The antigens "PT", "FIM2/3" and "FHA" appear to habe the widest range of values. 

> Q14. What antigens show differences in the level of IgG antibody titers recognizing them over time? Why these and not others?

The antigens that show the most noticeable differences in IgG antibody titers over time are PT, PRN, FHA, and FIM2/3. These antigens show higher MFI values at certain visits, especially after vaccination, and then gradually decrease at later visits, indicating that antibody levels change over time following the immune response. This occurs because these antigens are components of the pertussis vaccine, so the immune system produces antibodies against them after vaccination. In contrast, antigens such as OVA and DT do not show large changes because they are not specific targets of the pertussis vaccine, so there is little change in antibody levels against them over time.


